Confirmed cases of coronavirus in Nigeria is now 362 as 19 new cases were recorded on, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said. 14 of the cases were recorded in Lagos, two in Abuja, one each in Kano, Akwa Ibom and Edo. “As at 09:20 pm 14th April there are 362 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria,” NCDC said. “99 have been discharged with 11 deaths.” To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .